    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-05T09:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-05T09:40:00-05:00" n="243"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1221.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-05T10:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 5, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 3, 7 p.m. Respectfully suggest in addition to language in your
                    January 26, 3 p.m., the following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>To pass on and determine the validity of every debt, charge or claim of
                            any kind whatsoever; to countersign all checks, drafts or orders for the
                            payment of Dominican funds to every and all creditors; to decide whether
                            any particular debt about to be incurred is in violation of the treaty
                            1907 and to exercise all the powers and rights that usually attach to
                            the office of comptroller.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I may be wrong but I fear that when Dominican Government feels strong enough
                    financial expert would be given short shrift unless we are clear and definite in
                    defining his duties and standing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
